fields.name: PB90
fields.description: The Pro Bow is the bridge between our Low and the Mid Bow Sticks. It has been made to ensure that you have an edge with your 3D skills, without compromising on crucial consistent basic skills. Such as flat hitting and slapping.

fields.name: PB70
fields.description: The PB70 is ideal for those who prefer flair and control over power. The Pro Bow is the bridge between our Low and the Mid Bow Sticks. It has been made to ensure that you have an edge with your 3D skills, without compromising on crucial consistent basic skills. Such as flat hitting and slapping.

fields.name: MB90
fields.description: The Mid Bow (MB90) has been crafted to provide ultimate consistency and control with all skills, whatever your game situation is. It has an almost straight bow, which allows for unrivalled flat pushing, hitting and slapping.

fields.name: Duffle Bag
fields.description: The Otter Duffle bag is our original fan favourite bag. It is performs excellently in almost all weather conditions. It has multiple side holders to carry your sticks with, and a protective cloth layer over the tarp at the bottom so it doesn’t scratch. This extends the life of the bag. The shoe and shinpad compartment allows you to store your smelly shoes separately from your clean clothes and the discreet valuables pocket on the other side of the bag makes it even more useful. The bag also has backpack straps to make it easy to carry. But most importantly, it has a 70L capacity, so it can be used as a matchday kit holder and is perfect to use luggage for a week away!

fields.name: Otter Adventurer
fields.description: After the fantastic feedback from our duffle bag we've made a traditional style backpack that can withstand almost all the elements; but also, be fit for matchday and a long weekend away. Made with the same heavy-duty tarpaulin as the duffle bag, it performs great in harsh weather conditions and has a large 35-litre capacity. It can hold a stick in place using Velcro strapping on the side of the bag. This bag combines three key features from our Duffle Bag, Performance Pack and Urban Explorer. Tarpaulin material, heavy-duty looks and a buckle style system for extra security.

fields.name: Matchday Bag
fields.description: The Matchday Bag is inspired by our Duffle Bag, it uses the same materials, and it has more space than you could need. It has four large compartments, one padded pocket, one padded phone pocket and a Cool Zone to keep your drink of choice at the same temperature. We have included two carry handles, backpack-style carry straps and a side strap. The stick compartment can keep up to 6 sticks. The middle and top compartment are great for packing your kit in for match day. The bottom compartment can easily hold your smelly shinpads and shoes. This revolutionary new bag is simply amazing.

fields.name: Duffle Bag Lite
fields.description: This brand-new lite version of the duffle bag is great for training and the gym. It holds enough kit so that you don’t have items rattling around in your bag and has a 35-litre capacity It has multiple side holders to carry your sticks with, and a protective cloth layer over the tarp at the bottom so it doesn’t scratch. This extends the life of the bag. The shoe and shinpad compartment allows you to store your smelly shoes separately from your clean clothes and the discreet valuables pocket on the other side of the bag makes it even more useful.

fields.name: Matchday Bag Lite
fields.description: The brand-new Stick Bag Lite is inspired by our Matchday Bag, it uses the same materials, and it has a plethora of fantastic compartments. The stick compartment can keep up to 3 sticks. The middle and top compartment are great for packing your kit in for match day!

fields.name: Bench Coat
fields.description: Introduced for coaches & players that need some extra warmth in the winter. Velvet-lined pockets keep your hands nice and toasty. Triple lined, elastic insulating cuffs, & adjustable hood toggles for extra warmth. This is a water-resistant jacket.

fields.name: Puffer Jacket
fields.description: Warm, lightweight, winter sports jacket. Ideal for the pitchside & warmups. Includes four velvet-lined pockets to keep your hands warm & provide extra storage.

fields.name: White Hoodie
fields.description: Back by popular demand. This hoodie is great for cold winter training sessions & the clubhouse after a game.

fields.name: Black Hoodie
fields.description: Back by popular demand. This hoodie is great for cold winter training sessions & the clubhouse after a game.

fields.name: Training Top
fields.description: Made with Otter's new Dry-Fit material, found to dry up to 30% faster than our previous training tops. This makes for a better wicking fabric to draw more moisture away from the body.

fields.name: Tracksuit Trousers
fields.description: Skinny fit 50% cotton, 50% polyester tracksuit trousers for the ultimate comfort fit.

fields.name: MK9 Glove (Left Hand)
fields.description: This glove has been specifically made by us to provide you with unparalleled, lightweight left-handed glove protection; with the ultimate comfort fit. Why MK9? That's how many versions we had to make to get the balance of protection to comfort absolutely perfect.

fields.name: Toray Shinpads
fields.description: These shinpads offer the gold standard of protection and are used by our International Athletes. Toray Otter Shinpads made with premium carbon and polymer padding. The carbon keeps them light and strong, and the polymer padding adds an extra absorbing layer for added protection and enhanced shock dissipation.

fields.name: MK9 Glove (Right Hand)
fields.description: This glove has been specifically made by us to provide you with unparalleled, lightweight left-handed glove protection; with the ultimate comfort fit. Why MK9? That's how many versions we had to make to get the balance of protection to comfort absolutely perfect.

fields.name: Gribbid Chamois ProGrip
fields.description: Fresh from our collaboration with Gribbid, the number one grip used by internationals. 'The Gribbid ProGrip feels nice and gives an extremely good grip on your hockey stick, even when you have wet hands or when it rains. The chamois grip must be placed over the existing grip and is therefore also called an overgrip, (Gribbid, 2021).' 'Features: – Highest quality – Original progrip® quality from The Netherlands – Soft and comfortable – Shock-absorbing function – High moisture absorption capacity – Anti-slip under all circumstances – Suitable for all sizes of hockey sticks – Easy to apply and replace – Patented gribbid progrip® quality, (Gribbid, 2021)'.
